dbt-find-source-code

Interactive fzf picker over every resource (model, seed, test,
snapshot, source, analysis, exposure) in the current dbt project.
On selection, the resource's source file path is printed to stdout,
copied to the system clipboard, and opened in $EDITOR.

Each picker entry has the form:

  <resource_type>:<short_name>

where short_name is the dbt unique_id with the leading
"<resource_type>.<package>." prefix stripped. Examples:

  source:storytel_order_service.state
  model:dim_customer_demographics_latest
  test:accepted_values_book_metadata_latest_v2_book_type__abook__ebook
  seed:country_codes

This means you can narrow the picker to a single resource type by
typing the prefix, e.g. "source:" or "model:".

WORKFLOW
  1. Searches upward from the current directory for dbt_project.yml
     (skipping dbt_packages/ and dbt_internal_packages/) and for
     pyproject.toml.
  2. Uses the shared per-project nodes cache at
     ~/.cache/rlm-dbt/<project_key>/nodes.json. If the cache is
     missing, it is populated via "dbt ls --output json" covering
     every resource type. The same cache is shared with rlm-dbt-ls,
     rlm-dbt-run, rlm-dbt-build, rlm-dbt-test.
  3. Entries are sorted MRU-first using the shared pooled history at
     ~/.cache/rlm-dbt/history.tsv. A pick recorded by this command
     appears under the "dbt-find-source-code" command tag.
  4. The first entry in the picker is "--- REFRESH CACHE (cached
     ...) ---". Selecting it deletes the cache file, repopulates it,
     and re-enters the picker. History is preserved.
  5. The fzf preview pane shows the contents of the resource's
     source file (rendered by `bat` if available, `cat` otherwise).
  6. On confirmation:
       - The absolute file path is printed to stdout.
       - The absolute file path is copied to the clipboard (pbcopy
         on macOS, xclip / xsel on Linux).
       - $EDITOR is opened on the file.

KEY BINDINGS
  Enter       confirm selection
  Ctrl-P      cycle preview height (tall → short → hidden)
  Ctrl-G      abort the picker
  Esc / Ctrl-C  abort the picker (Ctrl-G also works under terminals
                 that swallow Ctrl-C, e.g. Ghostty)

ENVIRONMENT
  EDITOR            Required. The editor invoked on the selected
                    file.
  DBT_TARGET        Optional. dbt target name. Defaults to the
                    profile's default target, then "dev".
  DBT_USE_FUSION    Optional. When set to "1", invokes "dbtf" (the
                    Fusion binary) instead of "poetry run dbt".

PREREQUISITES
  - Must be run from inside a dbt project (a dbt_project.yml file
    must exist in the current directory or any parent, outside
    package directories).
  - poetry must be available in PATH and the project venv must
    include dbt-core (unless DBT_USE_FUSION=1, in which case the
    `dbtf` alias must point at a Fusion binary).
  - profile/profiles.yml must exist under dbt_project_root.

REQUIRES
  fzf, jq, poetry (or dbtf when DBT_USE_FUSION=1)
OPTIONAL
  bat (better-rendered preview), pbcopy / xclip / xsel (clipboard
  copy of the selected path)
